item.title: Why Aparna Subramonian believes being misunderstood is the greatest teacher
item.description: Tell us what you feel. Message us. Aparna Subramonian, a brand marketer, writer, and self-proclaimed quirky cat lover, didn’t grow up trying to fit in. She grew up thinking she's a boy, fell in love with her best friend in seventh grade, and later discovered she had ADHD. All while battling social mores in a small, conservative city like Coimbatore.
